		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>We present AROW, a new online learning algorithm that combines several useful properties: large margin training, confidence weighting, and the capacity to handle non-separable data. AROW performs adaptive regular-ization of the prediction function upon seeing each new instance, allowing it to perform especially well in the presence of label noise. We derive a mistake bound, similar in form to the second order perceptron bound, that does not assume separability. We also relate our algorithm to recent confidence-weighted online learning techniques and show empirically that AROW achieves state-of-the-art performance and notable robustness in the case of non-separable data.</p>
			</abstract>
